sentences: Ruth Berhe (born July 2, 1995), better known by her stage name Ruth B., is a Canadian singer and songwriter from Edmonton, Alberta.
She started by singing songs on Vine in early 2013.
In November 2015, she released her debut extended play, The Intro.
On May 5, 2017, she released her debut album, Safe Haven.
It has gathered over 1,151 billion overall streams on Spotify as of January 2022.
Her hit single "Lost Boy" has accumulated over 650 million streams on Spotify, and her YouTube channel has received a total of 368 million views as of January 2022.
Her song, Dandelions from Safe Haven became a sleeper hit in 2022, when it grew in popularity due to TikTok and charted in the UK and Worldwide charts.
Her parents emigrated from Ethiopia in the 1980s.
She spent some of her teenage years working at a local Reitmans clothing store and described herself in an interview with The Canadian Press as an "introvert".
Berhe graduated from Ross Sheppard High School in 2013.
